TestCase.Discription:
Hardware acceleration on 2D Graphics is enabled by default. However, not all 2D drawing operations ae supported, problems may occur as a side effect. Developers can switch off the acceralations at the app level or individual level - Activity, Window and View. The system must be able to enable or disable the acceleration according to the manifest file.
<br />Application Levle - &lt;activity android:hardwareAccelerated=&quot;false&quot; /&gt;
<br />Window Level - WindowManager.LayoutParams.FLAG_HARDWARE_ACCELERATED
<br />View Level - myView.setLayerType(View.LAYER_TYPE_SOFTWARE, null);
<br />
